/*
 *
 * Instagram feed display
 *
 * */

{% comment %}
Sizing is via flex. In general we want the images laid out horizontally
without needing wrapping, but it can wrap if needed.  The minimum width on
the top-level a element is where that would come up.

The base width of an image is set as a percentage of the parent based on the
configured number of instagram images for the theme.
{% endcomment %}

{% assign instafeed_img_pct = 1.0 | divided_by: settings.instafeed_limit | times: 100 %}

#instafeed {
  text-align: center;
  padding-bottom: 40px;
  padding-top: 40px;
  position: relative;
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  justify-content: center;
}

#instafeed p {
  font-size: 130%;
  text-align: center;
  width: 100%;
}

#instafeed > a {
  flex-basis: auto;
  width: calc({{ instafeed_img_pct }}% - 30px);
  min-width: 100px;
  padding: 15px;
}

#instafeed > a img {
  width: 100%;
}
